###What is Git ? 

- Free and open source version control system

###What is version Control?
- The management of changes to documents, computer programs, large web sites, and other collections of information.

###Terms
 - Directory  > Folder
 - Terminal or Command Line  -> Interface for text commands
 - CLI > Command Line Interface
 - Repository  > Project, or the folder/place where your project is kept (Basically Git Repository)
 - Github > A website to host your repositories online
 
### Git Commands
- clone  - bring a repository that is host somewhere like Github into folder 
on you local machine 
- add - Track your files and changes in Git 
- commit - Save your files in Git
- push - upload git commits to a remote repo , like github
- pull - Download changes from remote repo to your local machine, opp of push


## Basic Git Commands
- git -version
- git clone 
-  ls -la   -> to get hidden .git directory
- Untracked files - files not under git 
- Staged with Git using -  git add 
- Generate key for git 
    - ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "githubemailaddress"
    - for multiple accounts use different key name
    - will generate two keys - use pub key to upload on github
    - use this command -> pbcody < ~/<key-name>.pub  to copy to github

- git push origin master
    - to push the changes
   
- git push --set -upstream origin feature-branch 
-or
- git push -u origin feature-branch  

- git remote add origin <git@github.com:puneettandon/repo.git>

- git remote -v

- git push -u origin master

- git branch

- git branch -d feature-branch
    - to delete the branch
- git checkout -b feature-branch

- git diff 

- ### Delete Untracked changes git
  git clean -n 
    - If you want to see which files will be deleted you can use the -n option before you run the actual command

  git clean -f
    - Then when you are comfortable (because it will delete the files for real!) use the -f option

  git clean -f -d
    - To remove directories

  git clean -f -X
    - To remove ignored files

  git clean -f -x
    - To remove ignored and non-ignored files
  


- ### Head in Git
  

- ### History in Git
  - git show <commit-id>
  

- How to undo git add for certain file
  - If you need to remove a single file from the staging area, use
    - git reset HEAD -- filename
  - If you need to remove a whole directory (folder) from the staging area, use
    - git reset HEAD -- directoryName

  - If whole 
    - git reset HEAD

- ### How to make local and remote branches sync
  - suppose local branches have different commit than remote branches
  then use these commands
    - git fetch --prune origin 
    - git reset --hard origin/master
    - git clean -f -d  




    
    
